/*
**  Styling to override standard and gem default styling.
**
**  We are running the differences between the current edited rule and what is in the repo.
**  We do this by running the diffy gem.
**  The diffy gem, marks up the differences in ins tags, del tags, tags with class ins or del,
**  and strong tags for the part of the line which changed.
**
**  The standard styling for ins and del tags is underline and strikethrough.
**  The diffy gem has CSS you can include using an erb ruby call for green and red color.
**  This styling may be undesirable and need to be overriden.
**  The diffy colors, for instance, do not make a readable contrast.
*/


/*
**  Nesting:
**    Rule differences are in div.rule_detail_view section.
**    All diffy output will be under a div.diff section.
**    Lines are in li tags, with ins class for inserts and del class for deletes.
**    With the li, there are ins and del tags for inserts and deletes.
**    The part of the line which changed is marked in a strong tag.
*/


<%= Diffy::CSS %>


.diff ins {
  text-decoration: none;
}

.diff del {
  text-decoration: none;
}

.diff ul {
  list-style: none;
}


.diff li.ins {
  background:#dfd;
  color: #007800;
}
.diff li.del {
  background:#fee;
  color: #900000;
}

.diff ins strong {
  font-weight:normal;
  background: #aaffaa;
  color: #0d610d;
}
.diff del strong {
  font-weight:normal;
  background: #ffd4d4;
  color: #670505;
}

